bib_record.title: Evidence of non-statistical structures in the elastic and inelastic scattering of Ni-58+Ni-58 and Ni-58+Ni-62 and intermediate dinuclear states.

free_txt: Statistical analysis.The intermediate dinuclear
system approach.
-By authors. The contribution of each reaction channel
to the total cross section by fitting gaussian
functions was evaluated. For Ni-58+Ni-62 the data were
fitted with an overlap of four gaussian functions,
corresponding, respectively, to the elastic, single
inelastic Ni-58, single inelastic Ni-62 and the mutual
inelastic scattering. In the fitting procedure only
the amplitudes of the gaussian functions were left as
free parameters. The elastic and the various inelastic
scatterings are not fully separated. For Ni-58+Ni-58
the separation is sufficient to clearly distinguish the
elastic from the first inelastic peak and the
gaussian-fit separation is quite efficient. It is less
so for the Ni-58+Ni-62 case, the uncertainties in the
amplitude of the various peaks are taken into account
in the systematic errors and reflects themselves in the
large errors.
Two position-sensitive silicon detectors,
100-mum thick, 47-mm long and 8-mm wide.
The errors reported in figures takes into account both
the statistical and the systematic contributions.
Details of
experiment.
A 10-mug/cm**2 Ni-58 and Ni-62 layers evaporated onto
10-mug/cm**2 carbon backing served as target.
By CAJAD.
